CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1955, pg. 21, reads: "Little Leaguers Set - These youngsters, representatives of the Little League teams in Hill District, pose at Ammon Field prior to the opening of the season. Left to right: Charles Alexander, Lions; Paul Robinson, B & M Restaurant; Alfred Diggs, Whiteside; Jack Bishop, North Side Elks; Andy Blackwell, Fireman's; Eugene Snyder, Frank Galford, Junior Braves, and Joseph Lewis, Satans. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Little League baseball players from Pittsburgh Lions, B & M Restaurant, Elks, Fireman's, and Satans teams, from left: Charles Alexander, Paul Robinson, Alfred Diggs, Jack Bishop, Andy Blackwell, Eugene Snyder, Frank Galford, and Joseph Lewis, posed in gym, another version
